		<td><b>Can meaningful data be read from $2006?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Is it possible that the reads from $2006 return any meaningful information? Does anyone know anything about this?
<br />
<br />Thanks!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quietust</b> [ Fri Jan 20, 2006 10:11 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Reading $2006 does not return any meaningful data - it just happens to give you the last data that was recently* on the PPU I/O bus (i.e. the last value you read from or wrote to $2000-$2007).
<br />
<br />* the value likely decays fairly quickly

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

