	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Reading $2006 does not return any meaningful data - it just happens to give you the last data that was recently on the PPU I/O bus</div>
<br />
<br />I think this qualifies as meaningful (but not reliable). A game could even erroneously rely on the data, perhaps reading the correct register then attempting to read a write-only register shortly after and expecting the original data.

		

		</td>
